text: [Music]
my name is lisa chandler and i am an
amazon dedicated cloud engineering
manager for the aws intelligence team
i've been with aws for a little over
five years i was a government contractor
for 24 years in my government career aws
was starting to come into that
environment and i just thought the
technology was so amazing and i thought
how amazing would it be
if i could be on the cutting edge side
of it as opposed to the consumer side so
i reached out to a friend that i knew
that had recently gone from the
government space into aws like hey how
can i get in on this
and what he said to me was it's what we
did on steroids
so that initially like really drew me in
because one thing that i really really
wanted was to be able to do more i would
absolutely recommend this environment to
anyone that loves fast-paced anyone that
loves to learn just naturally you always
want to know how things work and i think
the biggest selling point for aws is
bring your ideas put time in your
calendar to think big and
you actually have an opportunity to do
that
my personal journey over the last five
years it has been something that i never
would have expected i have really
started to look at life in general in
terms of think big i would always look
at in the brochure and say i really want
to do that but i wouldn't try it once i
got there but i have become so attuned
to taking a risk and it working well or
if it if i take a risk and it doesn't go
so well i see that it's not the end of
the world and that has carried over into
my personal life as well and i have
found that life has been more enjoyable
because i have started taking more risks
and seeing the benefit of it
